1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 14=

3
00:01:44,260 --> 00:01:45,130
Who's there?

4
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:03,380
(99% Industrial Alcohol)

5
00:02:17,610 --> 00:02:18,260
No!

6
00:02:35,690 --> 00:02:36,500
It's you!

7
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:53,540
Tong?

8
00:02:53,780 --> 00:02:54,690
Tong?

9
00:02:57,730 --> 00:02:58,570
Tong?

10
00:03:02,170 --> 00:03:03,170
Tong!

11
00:03:06,380 --> 00:03:07,730
Tong! Where are you?

12
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:19,940
Tong?

13
00:03:21,340 --> 00:03:22,940
(You've always hated him.)

14
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:25,170
(I'll help you play out
this story to the end.)

15
00:03:29,010 --> 00:03:29,850
Tong!

16
00:03:30,730 --> 00:03:31,730
Tong!

17
00:03:32,940 --> 00:03:34,010
Tong!

18
00:03:35,220 --> 00:03:36,260
Tong!

19
00:03:51,980 --> 00:03:53,290
How should I

20
00:03:53,980 --> 00:03:55,380
make up the story now?

21
00:03:57,450 --> 00:03:59,690
You met Tong
and developed malicious intent.

22
00:04:00,340 --> 00:04:02,130
You killed her in a fit of rage.

23
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:04,170
And then, you fled.

24
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:08,940
Tomorrow morning, when I deliver food,

25
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:10,850
I'll discover

26
00:04:11,730 --> 00:04:13,410
a child's corpse.

27
00:04:19,370 --> 00:04:20,610
Flawless.

28
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:26,610
Darn it.

29
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:28,660
Cursed brat.

30
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:39,060
(Xianghui)

31
00:04:39,370 --> 00:04:40,340
Xianghui, what is it?

32
00:04:40,490 --> 00:04:41,780
We're heading to Honglong Plaza.

33
00:04:41,810 --> 00:04:43,580
We've arrived and are about to go in.

34
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:44,610
As for the details,

35
00:04:44,850 --> 00:04:46,100
we'll talk when you get here.

36
00:04:46,730 --> 00:04:48,410
We've notified the others as well.

37
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:49,980
Alright, see you in a bit.

38
00:04:50,780 --> 00:04:51,290
Let's go.

39
00:04:51,290 --> 00:04:51,850
Go.

40
00:05:30,730 --> 00:05:32,370
Why are there two cars here?

41
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:37,020
This car belongs to Xing's dad.

42
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:40,810
I don't know whose this is.

43
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:43,170
Xing's dad

44
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:45,140
really is here.

45
00:05:57,140 --> 00:05:58,020
Tong?

46
00:06:00,340 --> 00:06:01,250
Fei?

47
00:06:01,980 --> 00:06:02,930
No one's here.

48
00:06:03,610 --> 00:06:04,540
Fei?

49
00:06:04,810 --> 00:06:05,700
Tong?

50
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:08,050
Fei?

51
00:06:12,660 --> 00:06:13,580
Fei?

52
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:17,780
You're still running a fever.

53
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:21,490
I'm taking you home.

54
00:06:23,170 --> 00:06:24,140
Fei?

55
00:06:25,050 --> 00:06:26,220
Come out now.

56
00:06:32,490 --> 00:06:33,370
Fei?

57
00:06:34,140 --> 00:06:35,410
If you don't come out,

58
00:06:37,810 --> 00:06:39,540
Tong will be in danger.

59
00:06:45,980 --> 00:06:46,850
Tong?

60
00:06:50,730 --> 00:06:51,700
Xing's dad.

61
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:54,050
Tong?

62
00:06:56,370 --> 00:06:57,220
Fei?

63
00:06:57,340 --> 00:06:58,290
Fei?

64
00:07:00,140 --> 00:07:01,100
Judge Shen.

65
00:07:03,980 --> 00:07:04,780
Xing's dad?

66
00:07:05,580 --> 00:07:06,780
I'm sorry, Judge Shen.

67
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:08,490
I should've told you.

68
00:07:08,610 --> 00:07:09,540
What happened?

69
00:07:09,730 --> 00:07:11,050
Tong called me

70
00:07:11,370 --> 00:07:12,610
and said Fei was sick.

71
00:07:13,610 --> 00:07:15,610
When I got here, Fei had a fever.

72
00:07:15,980 --> 00:07:17,290
I wanted to take them to the hospital,

73
00:07:17,370 --> 00:07:18,660
but they refused to go.

74
00:07:18,850 --> 00:07:19,810
They even made me promise

75
00:07:19,810 --> 00:07:20,540
that I wouldn't

76
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:22,250
tell anyone where they were.

77
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:23,490
I tried to persuade them,

78
00:07:23,730 --> 00:07:24,980
but they wouldn't come with me.

79
00:07:25,460 --> 00:07:26,540
They insisted

80
00:07:26,730 --> 00:07:28,140
that I just bring them the medicine.

81
00:07:28,370 --> 00:07:30,100
So, where are Tong and Fei now?

82
00:07:30,980 --> 00:07:31,980
They should still be here.

83
00:07:32,140 --> 00:07:33,490
It was getting very late,

84
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:36,410
and my wife is away on a business trip,

85
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:38,610
so my daughter is home alone.

86
00:07:38,930 --> 00:07:40,250
I had to go back to be with her.

87
00:07:40,730 --> 00:07:41,540
While I was on my way,

88
00:07:41,540 --> 00:07:42,410
I messaged Liu Juan

89
00:07:42,410 --> 00:07:43,780
to come and pick up Tong.

90
00:07:44,290 --> 00:07:45,540
When I got back,

91
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:46,250
I heard noises.

92
00:07:46,250 --> 00:07:47,810
I thought it was them,

93
00:07:48,050 --> 00:07:49,290
so I rushed over to check.

94
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:56,780
Then whose car is this?

95
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:00,170
It wasn't here when I first arrived.

96
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:04,250
This looks familiar.

97
00:08:05,020 --> 00:08:05,810
Look at the back.

98
00:08:05,810 --> 00:08:06,660
I see it.

99
00:08:07,810 --> 00:08:08,900
Now I remember.

100
00:08:09,020 --> 00:08:10,100
I've seen this car before.

101
00:08:10,460 --> 00:08:11,220
This...

102
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,290
This is Li Xueling's car.

103
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:14,220
Who?

104
00:08:15,290 --> 00:08:16,370
Tong's stepfather.

105
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:18,460
This is bad.

106
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:20,290
Li Xueling...

107
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:21,900
Did he see my message to Liu Juan

108
00:08:22,610 --> 00:08:23,610
and come here?

109
00:08:26,370 --> 00:08:27,490
Tong has always insisted

110
00:08:27,490 --> 00:08:29,140
that Li Xueling
was the one who hurt her.

111
00:08:29,540 --> 00:08:30,290
Where...

112
00:08:30,290 --> 00:08:31,290
Where is he?

113
00:08:31,290 --> 00:08:32,460
Never mind that now.

114
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:34,370
Let's find the children first.

115
00:08:34,370 --> 00:08:35,300
Alright.

116
00:08:35,730 --> 00:08:37,490
I know where they were hiding.

117
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:38,610
I'll take you there.

118
00:08:38,610 --> 00:08:39,420
Let's go.

119
00:08:41,130 --> 00:08:42,060
Call the police, quickly!

120
00:09:11,250 --> 00:09:12,130
Tong!

121
00:09:12,530 --> 00:09:13,420
Tong!

122
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:15,100
Tong!

123
00:09:16,850 --> 00:09:17,770
Fei.

124
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,180
Untie me now.

125
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:20,130
Right there.

126
00:09:20,420 --> 00:09:21,130
Hurry.

127
00:09:25,650 --> 00:09:27,060
Be careful, Judge Shen.

128
00:09:31,730 --> 00:09:32,650
How much further?

129
00:09:36,530 --> 00:09:37,490
Just up ahead.

130
00:09:39,730 --> 00:09:40,730
I'm not going in.

131
00:09:40,940 --> 00:09:42,250
I promised I wouldn't tell any adults

132
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:43,820
where they are.

133
00:09:43,850 --> 00:09:44,980
Just tell them

134
00:09:45,130 --> 00:09:46,530
you figured it out yourselves.

135
00:09:46,610 --> 00:09:48,060
Let's just find them first.

136
00:09:49,220 --> 00:09:49,980
Alright.

137
00:09:56,700 --> 00:09:57,650
Fei!

138
00:09:58,060 --> 00:09:58,730
Tong!

139
00:09:58,730 --> 00:09:59,580
Fei!

140
00:10:00,180 --> 00:10:00,890
He's the bad guy!

141
00:10:00,940 --> 00:10:02,180
He's the rapist!

142
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:05,700
Run!

143
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:06,610
Quick, run!

144
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:09,130
Shen Xiezhi!

145
00:10:29,730 --> 00:10:30,340
Hurry!

146
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:53,250
It's a dead end!

147
00:10:55,610 --> 00:10:56,490
There's a door here.

148
00:10:58,730 --> 00:10:59,700
Open it.

149
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:10,580
Open the door!

150
00:11:14,460 --> 00:11:16,130
Xing's dad, stop this madness!

151
00:11:16,340 --> 00:11:18,100
Do you have any idea what you're doing?

152
00:11:18,890 --> 00:11:19,890
Come out!

153
00:11:20,370 --> 00:11:21,700
There's nowhere to run!

154
00:11:23,340 --> 00:11:24,340
Judge Shen!

155
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:27,610
Don't make things worse.

156
00:11:27,610 --> 00:11:29,220
The police will be here any minute.

157
00:11:32,340 --> 00:11:33,460
I didn't do anything!

158
00:11:34,250 --> 00:11:35,370
I'm innocent!

159
00:11:36,220 --> 00:11:37,650
You forced my hand!

160
00:11:37,770 --> 00:11:39,580
You're all trying to frame me,
aren't you?

161
00:11:42,420 --> 00:11:43,250
Fine.

162
00:11:43,850 --> 00:11:44,980
If you won't come out,

163
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:48,700
then you're never getting out!

164
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:01,940
Open the door!

165
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:03,820
If he catches those girls,

166
00:12:03,820 --> 00:12:05,060
they'll be in grave danger!

167
00:12:05,340 --> 00:12:06,130
Open up!

168
00:12:31,540 --> 00:12:32,540
(99% Industrial Alcohol)

169
00:12:39,730 --> 00:12:41,890
You've left me with no choice,
Judge Shen.

170
00:12:44,650 --> 00:12:46,700
Once I catch those little brats,

171
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:48,580
I'll send them to join you.

172
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:50,420
And if you're still upset...

173
00:12:50,980 --> 00:12:51,490
Open the door!

174
00:12:51,490 --> 00:12:52,490
I'll send Li Xueling

175
00:12:52,610 --> 00:12:54,010
to apologize in the afterlife!

176
00:12:56,460 --> 00:12:57,460
Judge Shen.

177
00:12:58,850 --> 00:13:00,180
Good luck to you both.

178
00:13:22,060 --> 00:13:22,940
He's setting a fire!

179
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:33,180
Find something to block the door!

180
00:14:10,180 --> 00:14:11,060
(Police)

181
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:15,490
Don't move!

182
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:17,250
Who are you looking for?

183
00:14:18,380 --> 00:14:20,300
- You've got the wrong person!
- Stay still! Don't move!

184
00:14:20,740 --> 00:14:21,100
Don't move!

185
00:14:21,100 --> 00:14:22,220
You got the wrong person!

186
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:55,750
Follow them!

187
00:14:55,750 --> 00:14:56,370
Move!

188
00:14:59,940 --> 00:15:02,220
(People's Hospital, Outpatient)

189
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:12,530
Son.

190
00:15:13,010 --> 00:15:13,820
You're awake.

191
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:15,610
Dad? What are you doing here?

192
00:15:16,340 --> 00:15:17,220
How are you feeling?

193
00:15:17,940 --> 00:15:19,100
Are you in any pain?

194
00:15:19,180 --> 00:15:20,220
I'm much better.

195
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:22,850
Hold on.

196
00:15:22,850 --> 00:15:24,460
Let me raise the bed for you.

197
00:15:29,340 --> 00:15:30,300
Is that better?

198
00:15:33,850 --> 00:15:34,850
You know,

199
00:15:34,940 --> 00:15:36,300
that was a very close call.

200
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:37,850
It could have ended worse.

201
00:15:39,650 --> 00:15:40,490
Here.

202
00:15:41,220 --> 00:15:42,130
Want some water?

203
00:15:53,010 --> 00:15:53,940
Son!

204
00:15:54,180 --> 00:15:55,370
You're finally awake.

205
00:15:56,530 --> 00:15:57,980
We were so worried about you.

206
00:15:57,980 --> 00:15:59,100
Look at your father.

207
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:00,850
He stayed by your side all night.

208
00:16:01,420 --> 00:16:02,490
It was so hard on him.

209
00:16:02,890 --> 00:16:03,770
He's exhausted.

210
00:16:03,770 --> 00:16:04,700
It's nothing.

211
00:16:05,700 --> 00:16:06,650
Actually,

212
00:16:06,890 --> 00:16:07,850
these past few days,

213
00:16:08,180 --> 00:16:09,420
I've been thinking a lot.

214
00:16:11,940 --> 00:16:14,220
When you lost your temper with me,

215
00:16:15,250 --> 00:16:16,340
I realized I'm to blame.

216
00:16:17,940 --> 00:16:18,730
Son,

217
00:16:21,370 --> 00:16:22,460
look.

218
00:16:22,610 --> 00:16:23,420
All these years,

219
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:25,220
I never meant
to make your life difficult.

220
00:16:25,220 --> 00:16:27,250
You've always been such a bright child.

221
00:16:27,980 --> 00:16:29,650
And now that you're a judge,

222
00:16:29,890 --> 00:16:30,820
your mother and I

223
00:16:31,010 --> 00:16:32,700
can see how hard you're working.

224
00:16:32,850 --> 00:16:33,530
Okay?

225
00:16:33,530 --> 00:16:35,460
You've made us proud.

226
00:16:38,460 --> 00:16:39,460
The truth is,

227
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:40,610
the reason

228
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:43,420
I was always so critical

229
00:16:44,010 --> 00:16:45,980
not because of what you thought.

230
00:16:45,980 --> 00:16:48,610
I wasn't worried about you embarrassing me.

231
00:16:49,010 --> 00:16:50,940
How could I even think that?

232
00:16:51,060 --> 00:16:52,890
My son is exceptional.

233
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:54,180
Right?

234
00:16:56,980 --> 00:16:57,980
I was just

235
00:16:57,980 --> 00:16:59,100
worried about you.

236
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:00,650
After all, in my eyes,

237
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:02,770
you've always just been a child.

238
00:17:04,010 --> 00:17:05,090
But

239
00:17:05,420 --> 00:17:06,730
after this incident,

240
00:17:07,220 --> 00:17:09,290
I finally understand.

241
00:17:09,860 --> 00:17:11,250
You've grown up,

242
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:13,290
and you're building your own career.

243
00:17:13,290 --> 00:17:14,860
I can't keep trying to control you.

244
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:16,900
Keep doing so

245
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:17,980
will only backfire.

246
00:17:17,980 --> 00:17:19,050
Professor Shen.

247
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:20,700
- Let me finish.
- After all that talk,

248
00:17:20,810 --> 00:17:22,530
you never made it to the point.

249
00:17:22,770 --> 00:17:24,090
What your father means is,

250
00:17:24,330 --> 00:17:26,530
he's not going to nag you anymore.

251
00:17:26,530 --> 00:17:28,250
Just focus on your work.

252
00:17:28,730 --> 00:17:30,330
If he starts nagging again,

253
00:17:30,570 --> 00:17:31,940
I'm done with him.

254
00:17:31,940 --> 00:17:33,940
I'll take Grandpa and move in with you.

255
00:17:34,730 --> 00:17:36,050
Please, no.

256
00:17:36,530 --> 00:17:37,980
My apartment is tiny.

257
00:17:37,980 --> 00:17:39,570
It can't fit all of you.

258
00:17:40,420 --> 00:17:41,250
Mom,

259
00:17:41,570 --> 00:17:42,420
you should really

260
00:17:42,730 --> 00:17:44,290
just stay home

261
00:17:44,530 --> 00:17:45,660
and take care of Dad.

262
00:17:45,770 --> 00:17:48,770
He can't even look after himself
without you.

263
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:51,810
Is that really what you think of me?

264
00:17:52,530 --> 00:17:53,530
Pretty much.

265
00:17:54,530 --> 00:17:56,730
Alright, don't worry.

266
00:17:57,050 --> 00:17:58,900
My injury isn't serious.

267
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:00,420
I'll be out of here soon.

268
00:18:02,770 --> 00:18:03,620
This weekend,

269
00:18:03,730 --> 00:18:04,860
I'll come home

270
00:18:04,860 --> 00:18:06,620
to have a nice meal

271
00:18:06,660 --> 00:18:07,980
with you, Dad, and Grandpa.

272
00:18:09,050 --> 00:18:10,460
Then, it's a deal?

273
00:18:10,530 --> 00:18:11,490
It's a deal.

274
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:13,420
Good.

275
00:18:35,940 --> 00:18:37,860
How are you doing, Your Highness?

276
00:18:42,730 --> 00:18:43,700
Where does it hurt?

277
00:18:45,180 --> 00:18:46,660
My head still hurts a little.

278
00:18:47,530 --> 00:18:48,460
A headache?

279
00:18:48,700 --> 00:18:49,860
It might be

280
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:52,700
symptoms of the concussion.

281
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:54,570
You were fine when I went out.

282
00:18:55,330 --> 00:18:57,380
Maybe we should go back for a check-up.

283
00:18:57,620 --> 00:18:58,490
Let's go.

284
00:18:58,490 --> 00:18:59,380
No need.

285
00:18:59,380 --> 00:19:01,290
I'll be fine with some rest.

286
00:19:02,140 --> 00:19:03,530
Look at how you're lying.

287
00:19:03,530 --> 00:19:05,050
Get comfortable.

288
00:19:05,530 --> 00:19:06,700
I'll go start dinner.

289
00:19:06,810 --> 00:19:07,810
You get some rest.

290
00:19:32,460 --> 00:19:33,530
What are you doing?

291
00:19:36,330 --> 00:19:37,490
It still hurts.

292
00:19:39,420 --> 00:19:40,620
What are you hiding?

293
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,420
Nothing. My head is just throbbing.

294
00:19:45,730 --> 00:19:46,730
What's that smell?

295
00:19:47,180 --> 00:19:48,420
Nothing. I don't smell anything.

296
00:19:48,660 --> 00:19:49,810
What's in your mouth?

297
00:19:50,490 --> 00:19:51,420
Open up.

298
00:19:53,860 --> 00:19:55,660
Nothing, I swear.

299
00:19:56,700 --> 00:19:58,530
Unbelievable.

300
00:19:59,490 --> 00:20:00,940
So your head doesn't hurt now?

301
00:20:01,050 --> 00:20:02,140
Look, it's just...

302
00:20:02,290 --> 00:20:03,380
I felt guilty

303
00:20:04,380 --> 00:20:06,770
for coming home and not helping

304
00:20:06,770 --> 00:20:07,730
with the cooking.

305
00:20:07,900 --> 00:20:10,220
Since when have you ever
helped me with that?

306
00:20:12,050 --> 00:20:13,090
I knew it.

307
00:20:13,730 --> 00:20:15,660
You definitely got home early.

308
00:20:15,810 --> 00:20:18,570
You were slacking off
and felt guilty, right?

309
00:20:18,660 --> 00:20:19,570
No.

310
00:20:21,420 --> 00:20:22,980
Okay, I was a little early.

311
00:20:23,090 --> 00:20:24,010
But I thought...

312
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,530
Well, my head really did hurt.

313
00:20:27,090 --> 00:20:27,900
I'm the one who's sick.

314
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:29,940
It's not a crime to buy some snacks.

315
00:20:30,290 --> 00:20:32,180
Then I ate in bed,

316
00:20:32,490 --> 00:20:33,860
and forgot to get up.

317
00:20:34,220 --> 00:20:36,050
And then you walked in.

318
00:20:40,290 --> 00:20:41,010
I promise

319
00:20:41,010 --> 00:20:43,330
it won't happen again.

320
00:20:43,810 --> 00:20:44,900
Cut the act.

321
00:20:45,380 --> 00:20:46,530
What?

322
00:20:47,090 --> 00:20:47,530
You...

323
00:20:48,010 --> 00:20:49,530
You didn't use to talk like this.

324
00:20:49,530 --> 00:20:50,900
It's like you're a different person.

325
00:20:51,420 --> 00:20:52,420
How am I different?

326
00:20:53,140 --> 00:20:53,570
Besides...

327
00:20:53,570 --> 00:20:55,050
it's good to change things up.

328
00:20:55,050 --> 00:20:56,700
It keeps life fresh.

329
00:20:58,860 --> 00:21:00,010
Strange.

330
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:02,330
It's just too strange.

331
00:21:05,290 --> 00:21:07,290
Ever since the fire,

332
00:21:07,330 --> 00:21:08,980
you've been a different person.

333
00:21:09,050 --> 00:21:10,140
How so?

334
00:21:10,460 --> 00:21:11,530
It's not like I transformed.

335
00:21:14,460 --> 00:21:15,570
Are you in love?

336
00:21:15,620 --> 00:21:17,180
As if!

337
00:21:17,660 --> 00:21:19,140
This isn't a novel.

338
00:21:19,290 --> 00:21:20,090
It's not that easy.

339
00:21:20,530 --> 00:21:23,530
The whole office has
heard about you two.

340
00:21:24,860 --> 00:21:26,290
The hero saves the damsel.

341
00:21:26,940 --> 00:21:28,250
What's going on
with you and Shen Xiezhi?

342
00:21:28,460 --> 00:21:30,090
What does he have to do with this?

343
00:21:30,090 --> 00:21:31,090
I'm with him

344
00:21:31,330 --> 00:21:32,490
every single day.

345
00:21:33,010 --> 00:21:34,290
What could possibly be going on?

346
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:36,010
We're just helping each other out.

347
00:21:36,010 --> 00:21:37,460
Helping the public.

348
00:21:37,620 --> 00:21:38,660
Serving the people.

349
00:21:39,050 --> 00:21:39,730
Fine.

350
00:21:39,860 --> 00:21:43,250
See? I knew this house
can't run without me.

351
00:21:44,180 --> 00:21:45,700
I'm going to start dinner now.

352
00:22:55,050 --> 00:22:55,980
Hang on tight.

353
00:23:11,810 --> 00:23:12,770
Three.

354
00:23:12,860 --> 00:23:13,620
Two.

355
00:23:13,770 --> 00:23:14,620
One.

356
00:23:27,220 --> 00:23:29,980
(Outpatient)

357
00:23:30,010 --> 00:23:30,810
Shen,

358
00:23:30,900 --> 00:23:32,180
Captain Jiang wants you to know

359
00:23:32,420 --> 00:23:35,250
that it's confirmed the suspect is
the same culprit from back then.

360
00:23:35,250 --> 00:23:37,490
He realized Tong had recognized him

361
00:23:37,530 --> 00:23:38,460
and grew desperate.

362
00:23:38,460 --> 00:23:39,620
He wanted her gone for good.

363
00:23:39,940 --> 00:23:43,980
Captain Jiang is compiling evidence
for all the cases to file a joint prosecution.

364
00:23:44,180 --> 00:23:45,330
We'll leave it to the police

365
00:23:45,330 --> 00:23:46,770
and the prosecution.

366
00:23:47,090 --> 00:23:49,180
They won't let him walk away.

367
00:23:49,490 --> 00:23:51,090
At least the kids are safe.

368
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:52,220
Judge Shen,

369
00:23:52,460 --> 00:23:54,330
you've been bedridden for over a week.

370
00:23:54,330 --> 00:23:55,420
You'll be discharged tomorrow.

371
00:23:55,420 --> 00:23:56,380
Are you excited?

372
00:23:56,380 --> 00:23:57,900
Will anyone be there to look after you?

373
00:23:58,660 --> 00:24:00,940
It's just a flesh wound.
I can manage on my own.

374
00:24:01,620 --> 00:24:02,530
Shen,

375
00:24:02,940 --> 00:24:04,090
what's really going on

376
00:24:04,090 --> 00:24:05,140
between you and Ms. Qin?

377
00:24:05,290 --> 00:24:06,770
What's going on between you two?

378
00:24:06,770 --> 00:24:07,570
Come on, tell us!

379
00:24:07,570 --> 00:24:08,860
Don't be silly.

380
00:24:09,660 --> 00:24:10,330
Yeah,

381
00:24:10,330 --> 00:24:11,730
it's clear things aren't ordinary

382
00:24:11,730 --> 00:24:12,810
between these two.

383
00:24:13,050 --> 00:24:15,490
You've got some explaining to do,
Judge Shen.

384
00:24:15,660 --> 00:24:16,980
I heard that night,

385
00:24:17,010 --> 00:24:19,530
Ms. Qin carried Judge Shen
out of the fire.

386
00:24:19,570 --> 00:24:21,420
They dropped from the sky

387
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:22,140
like they were...

388
00:24:22,140 --> 00:24:23,900
This is not a fiction novel.

389
00:24:24,180 --> 00:24:25,330
You have quite an imagination.

390
00:24:25,570 --> 00:24:27,180
Were you even there?

391
00:24:27,220 --> 00:24:28,660
Judge Shen is right.

392
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:30,530
Stop listening to rumors.

393
00:24:30,620 --> 00:24:33,330
If I hadn't seen it myself,
I wouldn't believe any of that nonsense.

394
00:24:33,660 --> 00:24:35,250
Did you even pass logic in college?

395
00:24:35,490 --> 00:24:37,330
How could a small girl carry

396
00:24:37,330 --> 00:24:38,330
a six-foot-tall man

397
00:24:38,330 --> 00:24:40,380
all on her own?

398
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:41,860
That defies the laws of physics.

399
00:24:43,010 --> 00:24:43,980
As a Master of Psychology,

400
00:24:43,980 --> 00:24:45,050
let me explain the reason.

401
00:24:45,290 --> 00:24:46,180
In extreme situations,

402
00:24:46,460 --> 00:24:47,660
human beings are capable of

403
00:24:48,380 --> 00:24:49,940
unleashing incredible energy.

404
00:24:51,380 --> 00:24:52,570
It was our very own Judge Shen

405
00:24:52,570 --> 00:24:54,330
tapping into that hidden power,

406
00:24:54,570 --> 00:24:55,460
grabbing Lawyer Qin

407
00:24:55,460 --> 00:24:56,530
and leaping into the void.

408
00:24:57,010 --> 00:24:59,220
Alright, alright, that's enough.

409
00:24:59,220 --> 00:25:00,090
Stop it.

410
00:25:01,460 --> 00:25:03,180
I'm going to say this one last time.

411
00:25:03,250 --> 00:25:05,380
There is nothing
between Ms. Qin and me.

412
00:25:05,570 --> 00:25:07,380
So please, stop asking.

413
00:25:07,660 --> 00:25:09,250
End of discussion.

414
00:25:09,380 --> 00:25:11,010
You're here to visit me, right?

415
00:25:11,180 --> 00:25:11,940
Fine.

416
00:25:11,940 --> 00:25:12,730
Alright.

417
00:25:12,730 --> 00:25:13,620
Have a seat.

418
00:25:33,160 --> 00:25:38,580
♪When a leaf can't find a place to fall♪

419
00:25:39,940 --> 00:25:41,780
(Mutton)

420
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:44,880
♪Wandering without a destination♪

421
00:25:47,220 --> 00:25:52,560
♪Until you appear and I see your eyes♪

422
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:53,420
(Court Courier)

423
00:25:54,330 --> 00:25:56,290
(3rd Floor Corridor)
I don't have any money!

424
00:25:57,900 --> 00:25:59,140
Why are you arresting me?

425
00:25:59,330 --> 00:26:00,660
You cheating scoundrel!

426
00:26:00,730 --> 00:26:01,460
I'll kill you!

427
00:26:01,570 --> 00:26:03,010
What are you doing? Stop!

428
00:26:03,490 --> 00:26:04,330
Listen up!

429
00:26:04,330 --> 00:26:06,660
Neither of you is fit to be a parent.

430
00:26:08,540 --> 00:26:11,740
(Disciplinary Interrogation:
A Practical Guide)

431
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:16,860
(Judge Shen)

432
00:26:22,320 --> 00:26:25,890
♪Lean on my tender shoulder♪

433
00:26:25,980 --> 00:26:27,660
(Qin Rui: Hello, Judge Shen.)

434
00:26:28,570 --> 00:26:29,900
(I heard you're still in the hospital.)

435
00:26:30,620 --> 00:26:32,250
(Are your injuries serious?)

436
00:26:32,850 --> 00:26:36,440
♪I'll be your shelter♪

437
00:26:36,460 --> 00:26:37,570
(Shen Xiezhi: Hello, Lawyer Qin.)

438
00:26:37,570 --> 00:26:39,860
(Thanks for asking. I'm fine.)

439
00:26:39,860 --> 00:26:40,980
(I'm being discharged tonight.)

440
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:44,860
(That's great!)

441
00:26:48,530 --> 00:26:49,460
(Qin Rui: That's great!)

442
00:26:53,660 --> 00:26:56,660
(About Ding Yajing...)

443
00:26:57,770 --> 00:27:00,050
(Shen Xiezhi: About Ding Yajing's divorce case
with Cheng Kuiyuan,)

444
00:27:00,050 --> 00:27:01,660
(if your client is available,)

445
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:03,700
(we can move
the online hearing to Wednesday.)

446
00:27:04,250 --> 00:27:06,140
(Qin Rui: Sure, that works for me.)

447
00:27:06,490 --> 00:27:08,770
(As long as
the defendant is fine with it.)

448
00:27:12,220 --> 00:27:14,700
(Shen Xiezhi: Okay, I'll have
Cheng Xianghui coordinate it.)

449
00:27:16,570 --> 00:27:17,240
(Qin Rui: Alright.)

450
00:27:31,340 --> 00:27:33,580
(Lian Mutton Soup)

451
00:27:34,010 --> 00:27:35,980
I've packed everything up.

452
00:27:38,730 --> 00:27:39,620
Fei has been out of school

453
00:27:39,620 --> 00:27:40,860
for over a week now.

454
00:27:41,010 --> 00:27:42,810
She should head back tomorrow.

455
00:27:50,090 --> 00:27:51,900
Fei is sleeping
in the private room upstairs.

456
00:27:53,330 --> 00:27:54,620
What's wrong?

457
00:27:54,620 --> 00:27:55,570
Why haven't you eaten yet?

458
00:27:57,090 --> 00:27:58,900
Is it not to your liking, or...

459
00:27:59,700 --> 00:28:00,770
Should I heat it up for you?

460
00:28:00,860 --> 00:28:01,570
No need.

461
00:28:02,220 --> 00:28:03,380
It's still warm.

462
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:05,380
I was waiting for you.

463
00:28:07,980 --> 00:28:08,860
Alright.

464
00:28:10,530 --> 00:28:11,490
Have a seat.

465
00:28:16,940 --> 00:28:18,010
You've put your stomach

466
00:28:18,050 --> 00:28:19,700
through the wringer, haven't you?

467
00:28:20,220 --> 00:28:21,530
Remember to grab a bite

468
00:28:21,660 --> 00:28:22,770
before you start working.

469
00:28:23,420 --> 00:28:24,620
We're middle-aged now.

470
00:28:24,810 --> 00:28:26,050
Health is everything.

471
00:28:26,570 --> 00:28:27,900
Otherwise, when we're old,

472
00:28:28,290 --> 00:28:29,420
I'll be stuck looking after you.

473
00:28:31,330 --> 00:28:33,620
Customers just keep coming in waves.

474
00:28:33,620 --> 00:28:35,460
I lose track of time when it's busy.

475
00:28:36,050 --> 00:28:37,460
That's an old habit of yours.

476
00:28:37,700 --> 00:28:38,980
You're too dedicated.

477
00:28:39,570 --> 00:28:40,770
You take the blame for everything.

478
00:28:40,940 --> 00:28:44,220
If even one thing is off
with the mutton, you take it personally.

479
00:28:44,460 --> 00:28:45,330
Of course I do.

480
00:28:45,810 --> 00:28:48,050
That flavor is my reputation.

481
00:28:48,490 --> 00:28:50,250
Alright. Eat up.

482
00:28:50,660 --> 00:28:51,460
Okay.

483
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:52,660
Let's eat.

484
00:28:56,620 --> 00:28:57,490
This is good.

485
00:28:57,900 --> 00:28:59,290
The grill master

486
00:28:59,660 --> 00:29:01,250
is getting much more skilled.

487
00:29:01,530 --> 00:29:02,530
He's really improved.

488
00:29:11,010 --> 00:29:12,010
I'm sorry.

489
00:29:12,010 --> 00:29:13,660
The boss lady says
we're closed for the day.

490
00:29:15,980 --> 00:29:16,940
Mr. Lian.

491
00:29:17,660 --> 00:29:18,490
Ms. Shu.

492
00:29:18,570 --> 00:29:19,860
Can we talk?

493
00:29:25,740 --> 00:29:27,980
(Lian Mutton Soup)

494
00:29:28,010 --> 00:29:29,490
How is Tong doing?

495
00:29:29,490 --> 00:29:30,530
She'll be discharged soon.

496
00:29:30,810 --> 00:29:32,700
Her vitals are all looking good,

497
00:29:33,180 --> 00:29:35,010
but she still needs time to recover.

498
00:29:35,330 --> 00:29:36,290
That's good.

499
00:29:38,050 --> 00:29:40,220
I came here today on behalf of Tong

500
00:29:41,290 --> 00:29:43,660
to offer your family

501
00:29:44,290 --> 00:29:45,290
a sincere apology.

502
00:29:46,180 --> 00:29:47,770
Over the years,

503
00:29:47,810 --> 00:29:49,180
Tong has caused Mr. Lian

504
00:29:50,140 --> 00:29:52,330
and your family so much trouble.

505
00:29:52,330 --> 00:29:53,420
I also want to thank you

506
00:29:53,420 --> 00:29:54,810
for pleading for leniency for her.

507
00:29:54,810 --> 00:29:56,570
Tong was a victim too.

508
00:29:57,290 --> 00:29:59,290
It was my fault.

509
00:30:01,050 --> 00:30:03,620
It's all my fault. I'm to blame.

510
00:30:04,330 --> 00:30:06,220
Why did I have to argue with her?

511
00:30:06,220 --> 00:30:08,250
Why did I get so worked up?

512
00:30:09,460 --> 00:30:11,420
That day,

513
00:30:11,860 --> 00:30:14,420
if I'd picked her up
ten minutes earlier,

514
00:30:14,420 --> 00:30:16,220
she wouldn't have walked home alone.

515
00:30:16,220 --> 00:30:18,530
None of this would have happened.

516
00:30:26,860 --> 00:30:28,250
Mr. Lian

517
00:30:28,820 --> 00:30:30,290
resigned as Deputy Chief Judge

518
00:30:30,300 --> 00:30:32,140
because of Tong.

519
00:30:32,770 --> 00:30:35,460
His bright future was ruined.

520
00:30:35,460 --> 00:30:36,330
No, no.

521
00:30:36,490 --> 00:30:37,810
Don't be so hard on yourself.

522
00:30:38,700 --> 00:30:41,380
Tong is traumatized right now,

523
00:30:41,530 --> 00:30:43,620
so please take good care of her.

524
00:30:44,490 --> 00:30:45,620
As for my resignation,

525
00:30:47,420 --> 00:30:48,730
it was my own choice.

526
00:30:48,860 --> 00:30:50,090
It had nothing to do with Tong.

527
00:30:51,140 --> 00:30:52,620
But then there's Fei.

528
00:30:53,090 --> 00:30:55,530
She went through so much trauma too.

529
00:30:55,900 --> 00:30:56,900
In any case,

530
00:30:57,180 --> 00:30:59,570
I've owed your family yoo much.

531
00:30:59,620 --> 00:31:00,900
I'm a woman too.

532
00:31:01,490 --> 00:31:02,770
I'm also a mother.

533
00:31:03,250 --> 00:31:05,490
I truly understand how you felt.

534
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:07,810
Fortunately,

535
00:31:08,010 --> 00:31:09,620
things have settled now.

536
00:31:10,620 --> 00:31:11,980
Let's all look forward.

537
00:31:12,420 --> 00:31:13,490
The past is in the past.

538
00:31:14,010 --> 00:31:15,010
We have to move on.

539
00:31:15,090 --> 00:31:17,860
Fei is doing well now.

540
00:31:17,860 --> 00:31:18,810
That's what matters.

541
00:31:19,900 --> 00:31:21,010
As for Tong...

542
00:31:22,290 --> 00:31:24,090
You have to stay strong.

543
00:31:24,090 --> 00:31:25,730
She's going to need you.

544
00:31:26,140 --> 00:31:28,290
If you ever need anything, just ask.

545
00:31:28,620 --> 00:31:29,570
Don't be a stranger.

546
00:31:30,250 --> 00:31:30,980
Yes.

547
00:31:31,420 --> 00:31:32,420
Anything you need.

548
00:31:54,250 --> 00:31:55,380
Judge Shen.

549
00:31:55,490 --> 00:31:56,700
Long time no see.

550
00:31:57,730 --> 00:31:59,380
Who are you? What do you want?

551
00:31:59,700 --> 00:32:01,620
Don't you recognize my voice?

552
00:32:06,980 --> 00:32:08,250
Do you have a grudge against me?

553
00:32:08,250 --> 00:32:09,620
Why are you being so rough?

554
00:32:09,700 --> 00:32:10,660
It's the middle of the night.

555
00:32:10,730 --> 00:32:12,570
If someone suddenly pops out
and pokes you,

556
00:32:12,570 --> 00:32:13,940
wouldn't you be scared too?

557
00:32:14,250 --> 00:32:15,770
I just came to bring you your crutch.

558
00:32:18,140 --> 00:32:19,460
But since you're so full of energy,

559
00:32:21,460 --> 00:32:23,220
I can interrogate you
without feeling guilty.

560
00:32:25,620 --> 00:32:26,490
Between you

561
00:32:26,860 --> 00:32:27,980
and that Ms. Qin,

562
00:32:28,570 --> 00:32:29,660
what's really going on?

563
00:32:30,570 --> 00:32:32,250
You've been dodging
my questions for a while.

564
00:32:32,490 --> 00:32:34,140
If I don't get some answers this time,

565
00:32:34,140 --> 00:32:35,620
I'm not letting this go.

566
00:32:38,050 --> 00:32:39,460
When I visited Ms. Shu,

567
00:32:39,460 --> 00:32:40,570
she told me everything.

568
00:32:41,180 --> 00:32:42,090
Confess already.

569
00:32:45,380 --> 00:32:46,700
Ms. Qin's firm

570
00:32:46,700 --> 00:32:48,220
is right across from the court.

571
00:32:48,460 --> 00:32:50,900
Nine out of ten cases
she takes are here.

572
00:32:51,140 --> 00:32:53,090
It's only natural
that we'd run into each other.

573
00:32:54,290 --> 00:32:55,570
Oh, how convenient.

574
00:32:56,530 --> 00:32:58,290
First, you two went to the outskirts

575
00:32:58,290 --> 00:32:59,330
to find a client.

576
00:32:59,330 --> 00:33:02,010
You got lost and
spent the night out in the cold.

577
00:33:02,420 --> 00:33:05,900
Then, the client had a breakdown
at the hospital,

578
00:33:05,900 --> 00:33:07,700
and you stepped in to save her.

579
00:33:08,290 --> 00:33:09,460
And soon later,

580
00:33:10,180 --> 00:33:11,770
you two were trapped in a fire together.

581
00:33:12,570 --> 00:33:14,660
She had a lead on Ms. Shu's daughter,

582
00:33:14,900 --> 00:33:16,220
so we went to investigate together.

583
00:33:16,220 --> 00:33:17,900
Yeah, yeah. Save it.

584
00:33:19,380 --> 00:33:22,220
Even if all those coincidences
were just random fate,

585
00:33:22,330 --> 00:33:23,420
I have to ask.

586
00:33:23,810 --> 00:33:25,490
After so many random events

587
00:33:25,490 --> 00:33:27,530
and surviving a life-and-death
ordeal together,

588
00:33:28,700 --> 00:33:30,180
has your relationship with her

589
00:33:30,180 --> 00:33:31,380
really not changed at all?

590
00:33:35,900 --> 00:33:36,700
Fine.

591
00:33:37,700 --> 00:33:38,620
Silent treatment?

592
00:33:43,490 --> 00:33:45,980
Don't forget what happened
with Lou Yue and me.

593
00:33:47,250 --> 00:33:48,980
We're just friends.

594
00:33:49,380 --> 00:33:50,490
I've said it so many times.

595
00:33:53,250 --> 00:33:54,460
It was just a placebo

596
00:33:54,460 --> 00:33:55,940
in a life-or-death situation

597
00:33:56,570 --> 00:33:57,490
during that fire.

598
00:33:58,090 --> 00:33:59,090
Do you understand?

599
00:34:00,770 --> 00:34:01,770
Think of it

600
00:34:02,380 --> 00:34:03,460
as humanitarian aid.

601
00:34:05,620 --> 00:34:06,490
Disaster relief.

602
00:34:07,140 --> 00:34:08,380
Even hospice care.

603
00:34:08,610 --> 00:34:09,490
Got it?

604
00:34:10,010 --> 00:34:10,980
Not at all.

605
00:34:14,980 --> 00:34:16,780
Check your logic before you speak.

606
00:34:16,900 --> 00:34:18,090
Disaster relief? Really?

607
00:34:18,900 --> 00:34:20,210
It was a low-probability event

608
00:34:20,210 --> 00:34:21,740
caused by an extreme environment.

609
00:34:22,780 --> 00:34:24,000
Like Zhang Wuji's parents
[*Characters from Jin Yong's novel]

610
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:25,170
being trapped on Ice Fire Island.

611
00:34:29,010 --> 00:34:29,900
Or imagine

612
00:34:29,900 --> 00:34:31,380
aliens took over the Earth,

613
00:34:31,380 --> 00:34:32,780
leaving only one man and one woman.

614
00:34:33,010 --> 00:34:34,570
For the sake of humanity's hope

615
00:34:35,010 --> 00:34:36,210
and survival,

616
00:34:36,690 --> 00:34:38,380
they'd have to fight to save themselves.

617
00:34:40,420 --> 00:34:41,650
You make it sound so real.

618
00:34:42,210 --> 00:34:43,260
But I don't buy it.

619
00:34:43,570 --> 00:34:44,570
Believe it or not.

620
00:34:47,130 --> 00:34:49,210
If I were in a life-threatening crisis,

621
00:34:49,780 --> 00:34:51,170
would you treat me like that?

622
00:34:55,780 --> 00:34:57,690
If you were in a crisis,

623
00:34:58,780 --> 00:35:00,420
your heart would still be with Lou Yue.

624
00:35:01,900 --> 00:35:04,820
Why do you always have to go there?

625
00:35:05,130 --> 00:35:06,050
See?

626
00:35:06,050 --> 00:35:07,130
I hit a nerve.

627
00:35:07,300 --> 00:35:08,690
I know exactly what's on your mind.

628
00:35:18,610 --> 00:35:19,690
You startled me!

629
00:35:19,980 --> 00:35:21,490
Why are you still here so late?

630
00:35:21,940 --> 00:35:23,340
Are you plotting a coup?

631
00:35:23,650 --> 00:35:25,050
Well, you haven't left yet either.

632
00:35:25,050 --> 00:35:25,860
I just came to check up

633
00:35:25,860 --> 00:35:27,170
on our hardworking lady.

634
00:35:29,260 --> 00:35:30,260
Stop being cheeky.

635
00:35:30,460 --> 00:35:31,610
You're just in time.

636
00:35:32,650 --> 00:35:33,980
At our meeting the other day,

637
00:35:33,980 --> 00:35:36,460
someone recommended a channel to me.

638
00:35:36,690 --> 00:35:37,460
For weight loss?

639
00:35:37,460 --> 00:35:38,380
No.

640
00:35:38,460 --> 00:35:40,340
If it's not for weight loss,
I'm not interested.

641
00:35:40,530 --> 00:35:41,820
Just watch and you'll see.

642
00:35:42,260 --> 00:35:44,300
This is a woman in her sixties

643
00:35:44,420 --> 00:35:47,010
(Rui's Legal Lens, Legal Livestream)
with her two stepsons in their thirties.

644
00:35:47,340 --> 00:35:49,050
The sudden death of the father

645
00:35:49,300 --> 00:35:50,300
has thrown the family

646
00:35:50,530 --> 00:35:52,460
into a unique kind of dispute.

647
00:35:52,780 --> 00:35:55,170
All things aside, for such a serious topic,

648
00:35:55,170 --> 00:35:56,940
isn't the band-aid
on her head a bit much?

649
00:35:56,940 --> 00:35:58,130
It's just a design choice.

650
00:35:59,780 --> 00:36:01,170
Wait, look at this.

651
00:36:02,650 --> 00:36:04,050
I've faced this lawyer in court before.

652
00:36:05,010 --> 00:36:06,010
I think I know the name.

653
00:36:06,210 --> 00:36:07,260
Her name is...

654
00:36:08,530 --> 00:36:10,650
She was the one representing

655
00:36:10,650 --> 00:36:11,980
Ms. Lin's husband.

656
00:36:12,460 --> 00:36:13,690
Her name is

657
00:36:14,490 --> 00:36:15,090
Qin Rui.

658
00:36:15,090 --> 00:36:16,570
"Rui's Legal Lens".
That's definitely her.

659
00:36:16,980 --> 00:36:17,980
Qin Rui.

660
00:36:19,570 --> 00:36:21,090
We actually go back a bit.

661
00:36:22,980 --> 00:36:24,050
So you're saying

662
00:36:24,210 --> 00:36:26,050
this is the lawyer from the case

663
00:36:26,610 --> 00:36:28,170
where she teamed up with Shen Xiezhi?

664
00:36:28,490 --> 00:36:29,380
Unconventional paths

665
00:36:29,380 --> 00:36:30,340
and unusual methods.

666
00:36:30,340 --> 00:36:31,570
That's the kind of lawyer she is?

667
00:36:31,780 --> 00:36:32,780
Yes, her.

668
00:36:35,090 --> 00:36:36,090
Mr. Liang,

669
00:36:36,490 --> 00:36:38,530
it looks like you lost to a young woman.

670
00:36:40,490 --> 00:36:42,010
No, no, it's a matter of principle.

671
00:36:42,010 --> 00:36:42,650
Listen.

672
00:36:42,650 --> 00:36:43,570
First of all,

673
00:36:43,900 --> 00:36:45,130
I did not lose.

674
00:36:46,300 --> 00:36:48,740
Second, we reached a settlement.

675
00:36:48,860 --> 00:36:49,940
And that was mainly because

676
00:36:49,940 --> 00:36:52,090
Shen Xiezhi was backing her up.

677
00:36:52,940 --> 00:36:53,380
Right.

678
00:36:53,380 --> 00:36:53,780
I know.

679
00:36:53,780 --> 00:36:55,210
You didn't lose. I get it.

680
00:36:55,210 --> 00:36:56,010
I didn't lose!

681
00:36:56,010 --> 00:36:56,780
Right, right.

682
00:36:56,980 --> 00:36:58,010
Don't talk nonsense.

683
00:36:58,690 --> 00:37:00,490
Losing isn't an option for me.

684
00:37:00,490 --> 00:37:01,690
It just won't happen.

685
00:37:01,860 --> 00:37:02,530
Alright.

686
00:37:02,530 --> 00:37:03,460
Never losing.

687
00:37:03,460 --> 00:37:04,420
I didn't lose.

688
00:37:04,570 --> 00:37:05,610
Don't stay too late.

689
00:37:05,610 --> 00:37:06,420
I'm fine.

690
00:37:06,420 --> 00:37:08,170
Since you're financially free,
enjoy your freedom.

691
00:37:08,170 --> 00:37:09,380
Sure, sure.

692
00:37:09,380 --> 00:37:10,650
Okay, bye.

693
00:37:10,740 --> 00:37:11,530
Bye.

694
00:37:12,650 --> 00:37:13,650
(Breast Department)
Dr. Bai.

695
00:37:13,650 --> 00:37:16,050
Is my wife's surgery
absolutely necessary?

696
00:37:16,050 --> 00:37:18,300
Generally, we must perform

697
00:37:18,300 --> 00:37:19,940
an axillary lymph node dissection.

698
00:37:20,170 --> 00:37:21,460
We won't be able

699
00:37:21,780 --> 00:37:23,130
to preserve the breast.

700
00:37:27,300 --> 00:37:29,340
I looked it up online.

701
00:37:29,570 --> 00:37:31,570
Prosthetic reconstruction
is an option, right?

702
00:37:31,690 --> 00:37:32,900
Reconstruction

703
00:37:33,010 --> 00:37:34,300
must be based on

704
00:37:34,460 --> 00:37:35,940
the effectiveness of the treatment.

705
00:37:36,570 --> 00:37:38,050
Due to individual physique,

706
00:37:38,130 --> 00:37:39,860
the body might reject the materials.

707
00:37:40,090 --> 00:37:42,010
There could be

708
00:37:42,090 --> 00:37:43,570
capsular contracture,

709
00:37:43,740 --> 00:37:45,460
pain, and other complications.

710
00:37:45,820 --> 00:37:46,650
So,

711
00:37:46,980 --> 00:37:49,050
you two should discuss it first

712
00:37:49,130 --> 00:37:50,940
before deciding on a plan.

713
00:37:51,860 --> 00:37:53,940
As long as she's okay,

714
00:37:54,130 --> 00:37:55,170
and it won't affect her health,

715
00:37:55,170 --> 00:37:56,380
we'll definitely go for it.

716
00:37:56,780 --> 00:37:58,610
But there's one more thing
I should tell you.

717
00:37:59,010 --> 00:38:01,650
Prosthetic reconstruction is
a cosmetic procedure.

718
00:38:01,650 --> 00:38:02,900
It's not covered by medical insurance.

719
00:38:03,210 --> 00:38:04,210
So you might need

720
00:38:04,530 --> 00:38:06,340
40,000 to 50,000 yuan.

721
00:38:08,130 --> 00:38:08,860
Forget it.

722
00:38:08,860 --> 00:38:10,650
No, no. We'll do it. Let's do it.

723
00:38:10,900 --> 00:38:11,940
We definitely should. Right.

724
00:38:11,940 --> 00:38:12,490
Good.

725
00:38:12,490 --> 00:38:13,490
I'll issue several

726
00:38:13,490 --> 00:38:14,820
pre-op examination forms for you.

727
00:38:15,300 --> 00:38:16,090
Also,

728
00:38:16,170 --> 00:38:17,740
next time you come,

729
00:38:17,820 --> 00:38:19,300
don't book a special needs appointment.

730
00:38:19,530 --> 00:38:20,490
To be honest,

731
00:38:20,490 --> 00:38:22,740
the 800-yuan fee isn't cheap.

732
00:38:22,980 --> 00:38:23,530
Alright.

733
00:38:23,530 --> 00:38:24,170
Thank you so much.

734
00:38:24,170 --> 00:38:24,740
Thank you.

735
00:38:24,740 --> 00:38:25,300
You're welcome.

736
00:38:25,300 --> 00:38:25,820
Thank you.

737
00:38:25,820 --> 00:38:26,300
Thank you.

738
00:38:26,300 --> 00:38:27,050
See you on Saturday.

739
00:38:27,050 --> 00:38:27,530
Alright.

740
00:38:27,900 --> 00:38:28,420
Take these.

741
00:38:28,420 --> 00:38:29,130
Thank you, Dr. Bai.

742
00:38:29,690 --> 00:38:30,300
Okay.

743
00:38:37,980 --> 00:38:38,740
Dr. Bai.

744
00:38:38,740 --> 00:38:39,610
You're here.

745
00:38:39,610 --> 00:38:41,780
Did you have something
to tell me in private?

746
00:38:42,010 --> 00:38:42,420
Yes.

747
00:38:42,420 --> 00:38:44,380
That is the case.

748
00:38:44,460 --> 00:38:46,260
Is my wife's condition not looking good?

749
00:38:46,340 --> 00:38:47,420
No, no.

750
00:38:47,490 --> 00:38:48,820
It's not what you think.

751
00:38:48,940 --> 00:38:50,780
It's just that I have
some personal matters

752
00:38:50,980 --> 00:38:51,740
to discuss with you.

753
00:38:53,300 --> 00:38:54,300
I thought

754
00:38:54,300 --> 00:38:55,690
there was a problem with my wife.

755
00:38:56,340 --> 00:38:58,050
Please, have a seat, Judge Ying.

756
00:38:59,420 --> 00:39:01,300
You know my profession?

757
00:39:03,090 --> 00:39:04,050
I hope you don't mind.

758
00:39:04,210 --> 00:39:05,860
I didn't intend
to approach you like this.

759
00:39:06,940 --> 00:39:07,780
The thing is,

760
00:39:08,130 --> 00:39:09,050
I recently

761
00:39:09,300 --> 00:39:11,460
had a dispute at Qingcheng Court.

762
00:39:11,570 --> 00:39:12,940
The court just informed me

763
00:39:12,940 --> 00:39:14,130
to attend a mediation next week.

764
00:39:15,210 --> 00:39:16,650
It's quite a coincidence.

765
00:39:17,570 --> 00:39:18,610
The Presiding Judge

766
00:39:19,130 --> 00:39:19,740
happens to be you.

767
00:39:22,200 --> 00:39:24,080
(Jindian Law Firm)
(Given that the party, Ding Yajing,)

768
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:25,050
(s currently abroad)

769
00:39:25,050 --> 00:39:27,780
(and cannot attend
due to objective reasons,)

770
00:39:27,900 --> 00:39:29,090
(after review by this court)

771
00:39:29,170 --> 00:39:31,130
(and with the consent of all parties,)

772
00:39:31,490 --> 00:39:32,610
(Online Hearing)
(this hearing)

773
00:39:32,610 --> 00:39:34,530
(will be held online
according to the law.)

774
00:39:35,940 --> 00:39:38,900
(Panel Judge, Court Clerk)

775
00:39:40,050 --> 00:39:42,210
I'll verify the information
of the plaintiff and defendant.

776
00:39:42,570 --> 00:39:43,610
Plaintiff's name?

777
00:39:43,860 --> 00:39:44,740
Ding Yajing.

778
00:39:45,050 --> 00:39:46,300
Please show your ID card.

779
00:39:47,300 --> 00:39:48,130
Will this do?

780
00:39:50,780 --> 00:39:52,690
Verifying the defendant's
identity information.

781
00:39:52,940 --> 00:39:53,820
Name?

782
00:39:53,820 --> 00:39:54,690
Cheng Kuiyuan.

783
00:39:55,570 --> 00:39:56,740
Please show your ID card.

784
00:40:00,610 --> 00:40:02,860
Verifying the identity
of the plaintiff's lawyer.

785
00:40:03,460 --> 00:40:04,010
Name?

786
00:40:04,010 --> 00:40:04,860
Qin Rui.

787
00:40:08,740 --> 00:40:09,650
Judge Shen.

788
00:40:10,810 --> 00:40:12,780
Are the identities of the plaintiff
and defendant verified?

789
00:40:12,780 --> 00:40:14,050
The facial recognition system
is working.

790
00:40:14,050 --> 00:40:15,420
I've also double-checked manually.

791
00:40:16,610 --> 00:40:17,690
Good. Have a seat.

792
00:40:17,690 --> 00:40:19,900
(Family Court.
Panel Judge. Court Clerk)

793
00:40:27,490 --> 00:40:28,380
Court is now in session.

794
00:40:29,380 --> 00:40:34,340
(Courtroom No. 6.
Hearing in progress)

795
00:40:34,340 --> 00:40:36,140
(Xia Lulu)

796
00:40:36,300 --> 00:40:37,330
(Court Clerk)
Judge.

797
00:40:37,650 --> 00:40:39,420
The plaintiff is showing
contempt for the court.

798
00:40:39,900 --> 00:40:41,530
She's over half an hour late.

799
00:40:41,570 --> 00:40:43,380
Does this count
as a withdrawal of her case?

800
00:40:45,010 --> 00:40:46,260
Ms. Shu, the call went through.

801
00:40:46,610 --> 00:40:47,900
Hello, is this Xia Lulu?

802
00:40:47,980 --> 00:40:49,130
Where are you right now?

803
00:40:49,610 --> 00:40:50,740
(Xia Lulu)
I'm not going.

804
00:40:52,860 --> 00:40:53,940
Are you sure?

805
00:40:54,260 --> 00:40:55,780
It'll be treated as a withdrawal.

806
00:40:56,010 --> 00:40:56,980
Who are you trying to scare?

807
00:40:56,980 --> 00:40:58,980
Wang Chenggui didn't
show up last time either.

808
00:40:58,980 --> 00:41:00,690
If he can do it, so can I.

809
00:41:00,900 --> 00:41:03,130
Tell him he's not getting
the upper hand.

810
00:41:03,130 --> 00:41:04,380
(Xia Lulu)

811
00:41:04,380 --> 00:41:05,300
Did you hear that?

812
00:41:05,570 --> 00:41:06,570
Did you all hear that?

813
00:41:06,900 --> 00:41:07,780
Who would ever

814
00:41:07,780 --> 00:41:08,940
want to live with her?

815
00:41:12,490 --> 00:41:13,490
Plaintiff, Ding Yajing.

816
00:41:14,820 --> 00:41:16,170
I'll verify this with you again.

817
00:41:16,490 --> 00:41:17,740
The house and the car

818
00:41:18,130 --> 00:41:19,380
shall belong to Cheng Kuiyuan.

819
00:41:19,940 --> 00:41:20,940
Confirmed.

820
00:41:22,260 --> 00:41:23,650
The mortgage will be paid by you.

821
00:41:25,130 --> 00:41:26,530
My income is a bit higher than his.

822
00:41:28,210 --> 00:41:30,300
Are you certain you want sole custody?

823
00:41:30,530 --> 00:41:31,690
And you waive child support?

824
00:41:31,900 --> 00:41:32,740
Confirmed.

825
00:41:32,740 --> 00:41:33,610
Judge.

826
00:41:33,860 --> 00:41:35,490
Didn't she just state it clearly?

827
00:41:35,820 --> 00:41:38,340
Just issue the mediation
agreement based on that.

828
00:41:38,380 --> 00:41:39,340
We both agree.

829
00:41:40,130 --> 00:41:40,900
Judge.

830
00:41:40,980 --> 00:41:42,050
I request a temporary recess.

831
00:41:42,050 --> 00:41:43,010
I need to

832
00:41:43,010 --> 00:41:44,260
re-verify the claims with my client.

833
00:41:44,860 --> 00:41:46,050
No need, Ms. Qin.

834
00:41:46,490 --> 00:41:47,460
I'm sorry.

835
00:41:47,490 --> 00:41:49,050
I thought about it all night.

836
00:41:49,050 --> 00:41:50,130
I think

837
00:41:50,530 --> 00:41:51,860
since we were once husband and wife,

838
00:41:52,010 --> 00:41:53,460
we should end this on good terms.

839
00:41:53,530 --> 00:41:55,170
I'll pay your legal fees as usual.

840
00:41:55,740 --> 00:41:56,530
Judge Shen, Ms. Qin.

841
00:41:56,530 --> 00:41:58,050
I know you mean well,

842
00:41:58,380 --> 00:41:59,570
and I'm very grateful.

843
00:41:59,570 --> 00:42:00,940
But as for the choices I've made,

844
00:42:00,940 --> 00:42:02,420
I don't really have any regrets.

845
00:42:03,260 --> 00:42:04,650
I feel that those eight years

846
00:42:04,650 --> 00:42:06,260
were just a small phase for me.

847
00:42:06,570 --> 00:42:09,420
I've lived through it,
and I've been happy.

848
00:42:09,530 --> 00:42:11,340
Since things have turned out this way,

849
00:42:11,340 --> 00:42:12,980
there's nothing left to cling to.

850
00:42:14,690 --> 00:42:16,530
Give him everything he wants,

851
00:42:16,940 --> 00:42:18,380
as long as I have the child.

852
00:42:18,570 --> 00:42:20,170
The child is the greatest gift

853
00:42:20,170 --> 00:42:21,650
in my marriage.

854
00:42:22,050 --> 00:42:22,900
Right now,

855
00:42:22,900 --> 00:42:24,340
I just want to end this relationship

856
00:42:24,340 --> 00:42:25,380
so that I can

857
00:42:25,380 --> 00:42:26,940
start my next journey.

858
00:42:27,130 --> 00:42:28,300
Judge Shen, I'm sorry.

859
00:42:28,300 --> 00:42:30,260
I have a few questions for my client.

860
00:42:30,380 --> 00:42:31,210
Go ahead.

861
00:42:31,380 --> 00:42:32,380
Hello, Ms. Ding.

862
00:42:32,940 --> 00:42:35,740
Is your right hand any better?

863
00:42:36,050 --> 00:42:36,610
I'm sorry.

864
00:42:36,610 --> 00:42:38,980
I burned you when you were at my firm.

865
00:42:39,460 --> 00:42:41,210
I promised to reimburse
your medical fees.

866
00:42:41,650 --> 00:42:43,380
Show me the receipt.

867
00:42:46,980 --> 00:42:48,690
Plaintiff's lawyer, this is unrelated...

868
00:42:49,130 --> 00:42:50,050
Let her ask.

869
00:42:50,420 --> 00:42:52,170
Plaintiff's lawyer, continue.

870
00:42:53,050 --> 00:42:53,940
Ms. Ding.

871
00:42:54,610 --> 00:42:55,570
I misspoke.

872
00:42:55,740 --> 00:42:57,170
I remember it was the left hand.

873
00:43:00,690 --> 00:43:01,420
Judge Shen.

874
00:43:01,420 --> 00:43:03,690
I have reason to suspect
that the plaintiff is not my client.

875
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

876
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

877
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

878
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

879
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

880
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

881
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

882
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

883
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

884
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

885
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

886
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

887
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

888
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

889
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

890
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

891
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

892
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

893
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

894
